---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Why Melodies Feel Like Memories — Art";
const updated = "Updated: 2026";
---

<Layout title={title}>
  <article class="page">
    <!-- HERO -->
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="hero-top">
        <a class="back" href="/art">← Back to Art</a>
        <span class="chip chip--music">MUSIC</span>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-left">
          <h1>Why Melodies Feel Like Memories</h1>
          <p class="lead">Melodies don’t just sound nice — they feel personal. The trick is how the brain predicts patterns, stores emotion, and replays memory-like fragments.</p>

          <div class="meta">
            <span class="meta-pill">Harmony • Emotion</span>
            <span class="meta-pill">{updated}</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-right card">
          <img class="hero-img" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1511379938547-c1f69419868d?w=200&q=80" alt="Why Melodies Feel Like Memories" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="hero-img-cap">Melody as pattern + emotion.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- TLDR -->
    <section class="card section">
      <h2>TL;DR</h2>
      <div class="tldr">
        <div class="tldr-item">
          <div class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div>
            <h3>Prediction creates pleasure</h3>
            <p>Your brain rewards accurate guesses; a melody is a stream of small predictions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tldr-item">
          <div class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div>
            <h3>Emotion tags the pattern</h3>
            <p>Hormones + attention stamp certain intervals and rhythms as “meaningful”.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tldr-item">
          <div class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div>
            <h3>Repetition builds ownership</h3>
            <p>Hearing a motif again feels like meeting a familiar person — even in a new song.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BODY -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="card pad">
          <h2>The brain loves patterns (especially moving ones)</h2>
          <p>A melody is a line through time. Unlike a painting you can scan freely, music forces sequence — and sequence is where prediction lives.</p>
          <p>When a melody sets up expectations (scale, rhythm, contour) and then confirms or gently surprises them, you feel “rightness” or “wow.”</p>

          <div class="callouts">
            <div class="callout">
              <h4>Try this</h4>
              <p>Hum a 5-note motif. Repeat it, then change just the last note. Notice how huge that tiny change feels.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="callout">
              <h4>Key idea</h4>
              <p>Meaning often comes from contrast: the same motif in a new harmony can feel like the same character in a different scene.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card pad">
          <h2>What composers exploit</h2>
          <p>Good melodies balance familiarity and novelty — enough repetition to be remembered, enough variation to stay alive.</p>

          <div class="grid3">
            <div class="mini">
              <b>Contour</b>
              <p>Up/down shape matters more than exact notes — it’s why you recognize tunes even when sung off-key.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mini">
              <b>Motif</b>
              <p>A short cell that can be stretched, inverted, or moved to another key without losing identity.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mini">
              <b>Cadence</b>
              <p>Endings signal “stop” or “continue” — closure is a powerful emotional cue.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="card section">
      <h2>FAQ</h2>

      <div class="faq">
        <details>
          <summary>Why do some melodies feel “sad”?</summary>
          <p>Certain intervals and slow, falling contours often mimic speech prosody associated with low energy and grief.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Why do I get songs stuck in my head?</summary>
          <p>The brain loops unresolved patterns; repetition + a clear hook makes it easy to rehearse unconsciously.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Does music work without lyrics?</summary>
          <p>Yes — because structure, tension, and release can communicate emotion without explicit language.</p>
        </details>
      </div>

      <div class="footnav">
        <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/art">← Back to Art</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/art/composition-in-painting">Composition: How Paintings Control Your Eyes →</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>

  <style>
    .page{ max-width: 980px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 24px 16px 60px; }
    .hero{ display:flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; margin-top: 10px; }
    .hero-top{ display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; }
    .back{ color: rgba(11,11,15,0.62); text-decoration:none; font-size: 14px; }
    .back:hover{ text-decoration: underline; }

    .chip{
      font-size: 12px;
      letter-spacing: .14em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 8px 10px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(245,245,247,0.9);
      border: 1px solid rgba(11,11,15,0.08);
    }
    .chip--music{ box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.02), inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(120,90,255,0.22); }
    .chip--painting{ box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.02), inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,120,90,0.22); }
    .chip--architecture{ box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.02), inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(90,180,255,0.22); }
    .chip--film{ box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.02), inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,200,90,0.22); }
    .chip--design{ box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.02), inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(90,255,190,0.22); }
    .chip--photography{ box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.02), inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(160,160,160,0.30); }

    .hero-grid{ display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1.2fr .8fr; gap: 14px; align-items: stretch; }
    h1{ font-size: 44px; line-height: 1.05; margin: 0; }
    .lead{ font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.72); margin: 10px 0 0; }
    .meta{ margin-top: 14px; display:flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
    .meta-pill{
      font-size: 12px;
      padding: 7px 10px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(245,245,247,0.8);
      border: 1px solid rgba(11,11,15,0.08);
      color: rgba(11,11,15,0.70);
    }

    .card{
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.72);
      border: 1px solid rgba(11,11,15,0.08);
      border-radius: 18px;
      box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .hero-img{ width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; display:block; min-height: 220px; }
    .hero-img-cap{
      padding: 10px 12px;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: rgba(11,11,15,0.62);
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(11,11,15,0.08);
      background: rgba(245,245,247,0.65);
    }

    .section{ margin-top: 14px; }
    .section h2{ font-size: 20px; margin: 0 0 10px; }
    .pad{ padding: 16px; }
    .section.card{ padding: 16px; }

    .tldr{ display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 10px; }
    .tldr-item{ display:flex; gap: 10px; align-items: flex-start; padding: 10px 10px; border-radius: 14px; background: rgba(245,245,247,0.6); border: 1px solid rgba(11,11,15,0.06); }
    .dot{ width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 999px; margin-top: 6px; background: rgba(11,11,15,0.28); }
    .tldr-item h3{ font-size: 14px; margin: 0; }
    .tldr-item p{ margin: 6px 0 0; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.68); }

    .two-col{ display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 14px; }
    .two-col p{ font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.75; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.72); margin: 10px 0 0; }
    .callouts{ display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 10px; margin-top: 14px; }
    .callout{ padding: 12px; border-radius: 14px; background: rgba(245,245,247,0.7); border: 1px solid rgba(11,11,15,0.06); }
    .callout h4{ margin: 0; font-size: 13px; }
    .callout p{ margin: 6px 0 0; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.66); }

    .grid3{ display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 10px; margin-top: 12px; }
    .mini{ padding: 12px; border-radius: 14px; background: rgba(245,245,247,0.65); border: 1px solid rgba(11,11,15,0.06); }
    .mini b{ font-size: 13px; }
    .mini p{ margin: 6px 0 0; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.66); }

    .faq{ display:grid; gap: 10px; }
    details{ border: 1px solid rgba(11,11,15,0.08); border-radius: 14px; padding: 10px 12px; background: rgba(245,245,247,0.55); }
    details summary{ cursor:pointer; list-style:none; font-weight: 600; }
    details summary::-webkit-details-marker{ display:none; }
    details p{ margin: 10px 0 0; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgba(11,11,15,0.62); }

    .footnav{ margin-top: 16px; display:flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; }
    .btn{
      display:inline-flex;
      align-items:center;
      justify-content:center;
      gap: 8px;
      padding: 10px 12px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(11,11,15,0.10);
      background: rgba(11,11,15,0.92);
      color: white;
      text-decoration:none;
      font-size: 14px;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .btn:hover{ opacity: 0.92; }
    .btn--ghost{ background: rgba(245,245,247,0.75); color: rgba(11,11,15,0.86); }

    @media (max-width: 900px){
      .hero-grid{ grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .two-col{ grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
    @media (max-width: 480px){
      h1{ font-size: 34px; }
      .footnav{ flex-direction: column; }
      .btn{ width: 100%; }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
